                  , <rs id="t17760221-58-viclabel319" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760221-58-victim571 t17760221-58-viclabel319"></join>, on the <rs id="t17760221-58-cd320" type="crimeDate">29th of January</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760221-58-off318 t17760221-58-cd320"></join> about the hour of one in the night, and stealing a feather-bed, value six shillings, a pillowcase, value six-pence, two linen sheets, value two shillings, three blankets, value three shillings, and a copper coal skuttle, value one shilling, the property of 
                     <persName id="t17760221-58-person572">
                        Margaret
                         Fisher
                     <interp inst="t17760221-58-person572" type="surname" value="Fisher"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17760221-58-person572" type="given" value="Margaret"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17760221-58-person572" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  ; a silver watch, value thirty shillings, eighteen linen shirts, value eighteen shillings, a cloth coat, value two shillings, a cloth waistcoat, value one shilling, a worsted waistcoat, value six-pence, a pair of velveret breeches, value two shillings, four pair of mens leather shoes, value five shillings, a muslin neckcloth, value six-pence, a blue woollen apron, value one shilling, three crown pieces in money numbered, the property of 
                     
                        <persName id="t17760221-58-victim574" type="victimName">
                           James
